TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {62268=Brown University Athletics | 235 Hope St. Box 1932 | Providence, RI 02912, 23807=Before Brown: A four-year starter at RHAM High School, Whalen also played basketball for one season … Captained the team as both a junior and a senior, Whalen was named CIAC All-Conference and All-State both years … Also selected to the Hartford Courant All-Courant Boys Soccer Team … Led the team in goals (7) in 2010, earning Sport Spotlight Player to Watch honors … Also led the squad in goals (6) in 2009 and was named a Hartford Courant Player to Watch … Earned Most Improved honors in 2008 and was a Northwest Conference All-Academic selection … Played club soccer for Oakwood SC Academy, where he served as a team captain in 2011-12 … Named Mystic Pizza Player of the Week once during the season … Personal: The son of James and Brenda Whalen, Tim has one brother, Joe … National Honor Society member while at RHAM High School … Concentrating in Environmental Studies.
